Community-driven toolkit for exploring and creating **Battlefield 6 mods**, focused on **safe modding**, **asset inspection**, and **offline-friendly customization**.

> ⚠️ **Disclaimer:** This project is intended for **educational purposes**, modding research, and customization in **offline / private environments** only.  
> Cheats, exploits, multiplayer advantages, and anti-cheat bypassing are **NOT supported**.

---

## ✨ Features

- 📦 **Asset Explorer** — browse extracted game assets (textures, audio, UI files)
- 🎨 **Cosmetic Mod Support** — experiment with skins, UI themes, HUD tweaks
- 🗂️ **Package Tools** — unpack / repack supported archive formats
- 🔍 **Frostbite Structure Research** — file signatures & metadata analysis
- 🧩 **Plugin System** — extend functionality with custom modules
- 🛠️ **Config Tweaks** — manage local configuration presets
- 📄 **Logging & Debugging Tools** — verbose output for modding workflows

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Requirements

- Windows 10/11 (recommended)
- Battlefield 6 installed locally
- .NET 8 Runtime *(if applicable)*
- Python 3.11+ *(optional for scripts)*

